-- U.K. Stocks Climb; FTSE 100 Gains 0.5 Percent in London
-- B y   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 2012-04-11T10:00:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-11/u-k-stocks-climb-ftse-100-gains-0-5-percent-in-london.html
U.K. stocks advanced, sending the
FTSE 100 Index up from its lowest level this year, as banks and
mining companies advanced.  The benchmark gauge gained 0.5 percent to 5,622.45 at 10:57
a.m. in  London  after swinging between gains and losses more than
five times today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
